t4818.text: When we told her our doctor refused to see us and sent us here, she said she wasn’t surprised. Apparently doctors all over Melbourne have even been refusing to see Asian patients in general, whether they’re from China or travelled recently at all.

t4819.text: We’ve had our temps checked and BP done, and now just a waiting game.

t4820.text: Even the staff had triage nurses are wearing masks for the most part, and are very regularly wiping everything down with sanitising wipes.

t4821.text: Interestingly the masks are a precaution but maybe not a good one. They don’t yet know if a mask will catch the virus, but better than nothing, and as it’s extremely unlikely J has the Coronavirus, and just has a flu, it’ll help a little.

t4822.text: They gave us better face masks as J has presented with a flu, and I have mild cold symptoms. About half of the waiting room has the same masks on. The triage nurse let us know they keep running out of them as people keep coming in the get them.

t4823.text: There’s also a big sign on the Administration desk saying “if you are presenting after travel from China on flight C2321 arriving 19/1/20 please put a face mask on and let the administrative Clark know”. It’s repeated below in Chinese.

t4824.text: We’ve presented to the Royal Melbourne ED on the advice of the doctor, on arriving there’s a nurse asking every person through the door if they’ve travelled to China in the last 3 weeks. Can’t entirely hear but so far I haven’t heard a yes.
